        "Web source 2",
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.baysidehistorical.org/about-bhs"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Gloria Swanson once called 216‑07 40th Avenue her home, linking Bayside to the silent‑film era’s most celebrated actress.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayside%2C_Queens"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Bayside’s quiet streets once attracted writers, actors, and musicians from Manhattan’s theater guilds, offering a retreat from the city’s bustle.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
